title: Charges against CM serious, will act if I get complaint, says Kerala governor
HP Congress chief backs her minister son over vendors' name order
After attack, Bengal junior doctors threaten return to cease-work
Centre lifts non-basmati white rice export ban, fixes MEP
30 yrss on, Guj court acquits 3 accused of spreading terror in post-Babri riots
9 religious structures on government land razed near Somnath temple
Illegal land hoarding hurt development in the hills: U'khand CM Dhami
Boost for Akhilesh as SP to get 2 front row seats in Lok Sabha, Congress 4
Probe against Kolkata cops after HC slams faulty rape inquiry
Gujarat lifts midnight cap on garba events

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during a rally in Jammu, promised voters that a full-majority BJP government is on the horizon. He highlighted this as a historic chance for the region to elect its own government and break free from decades of neglect and dynastic politics by Valley-based parties.
title: J&K set to get a majority BJP government for 1st time: PM Modi
Country’s first memorial for Military Intelligence personnel up in Pune
FIR against FM Sitharaman over poll bonds 'extortion', Cong seeks ouster

description: A Mumbai-based eye surgeon performed an operation on a blind man from Lahore at an eye hospital in Colombo due to visa issues preventing treatment in India. With help from a local surgeon, the operation restored partial vision within 48 hours. The patient had been unable to see his family for four years.
title: Pakistan patient, Indian doctor and eye operation in Sri Lanka
'Karma’ that Pak ills are consuming its own society: Jaishankar at UNGA

description: European tourists in Jammu and Kashmir have been struck by the region's peace and serenity amid local elections. Their experiences, such as houseboat rides on Dal Lake, mark a stark contrast to previous visits during times of turmoil.
title: Band of 10 from Europe struck by J&K’s ‘peace and serenity’

description: The Supreme Court of India has unveiled a handbook to combat stereotypes about disabilities in legal contexts. Chief Justice Dhananjay Chandrachud highlighted the necessity of respectful language and improved data collection on children with disabilities. The handbook discourages derogatory terms and endorses a people-first approach when addressing persons with disabilities.
title: SC handbook lists terms to avoid to refer to persons with disabilities
NSCS takes charge of cybersecurity oversight in India

description: Priyanka Gandhi criticized the BJP for using Jammu and Kashmir as a 'political pawn', promising to restore the Darbar Move and statehood if Congress is elected. She pledged to end smart meter installations, waive pending bills, and resume the rehabilitation process for Kashmir Pandits initiated during Dr Manmohan Singh's tenure.
title: Will ensure restoration of statehood in J&K, says Priyanka Gandhi
Sonrise in DMK, Tamil Nadu: Stalin appoints Udayanidhi deputy CM
J&K police head constable killed in Kathua, 2 terrorists dead in Kulgam

description: ​"My working day may not be your working day. Please do not feel obliged to reply to this email outside your normal working hours," Meghan writes this in her mails. Her staff claimed she is flexible and fair-minded like that. Meghan has around 16 staffers working for production on various Netflix projects, podcasts, the Archewell Foundation, and communications. Meghan shares credit and writes personal email thanking her staff for their contribution, an ex-staffer said.
title: Meghan Markle sends emails to her staff at 5 am but is kind enough to...

description: Mayank Yadav from Delhi has been called up to the Indian cricket team for the T20I series against Bangladesh. Known for his fast bowling, he gained attention during IPL 2024 with Lucknow Super Giants. Despite injuries, he persevered through a rigorous rehabilitation program and now looks forward to making an impact internationally.
title: Mayank Yadav's journey to his first India call-up

description: The Trovant stones of Romania, found in Costești, are remarkable for their ability to grow, move, and reproduce. Formed millions of years ago, these unique stones expand after rainfall due to a chemical reaction with minerals in the water. Over time, small stones called “microtrovants” form on the surface of larger ones, eventually breaking off to grow independently. These mysterious "living stones" continue to fascinate scientists and tourists alike, with research ongoing to uncover their secrets.
title: Mysterious living stones that grow, move, and reproduce

description: Junior doctors in West Bengal are set to resume their 'cease work' protest following a Supreme Court hearing regarding the alleged rape and murder of a postgraduate trainee doctor. The decision comes after an assault on hospital staff at Sagar Dutta Hospital, sparking renewed calls for justice and safety reforms.
title: RG Kar case: Bengal junior docs to resume 'cease work' on Monday

description: The Pittsburgh Steelers are currently starting Justin Fields at quarterback as Russell Wilson rests his calf injury. With a strong 3-0 start, Fields has impressed both fans and teammates. There are discussions about making him the long-term starter. Meanwhile, the Miami Dolphins have shown interest in trading for Wilson if Tua Tagovailoa remains sidelined.
title: ​Pittsburgh Steelers Embrace Justin Fields as starting quarterback

description: Mahendra Singh Dhoni will be treated as an 'uncapped' player for the 2025 IPL under new rules from the league's governing council. Franchises can retain up to six players, with an increased auction purse of Rs 120 crore. Other changes include match fees and regulations affecting overseas players.
title: Dhoni to be 'uncapped' player as IPL retention rules announced

description: SpaceX initiated a mission to retrieve astronauts Butch Wilmore and Sunita Williams from the ISS following safety concerns with their Boeing spacecraft. Nasa’s Nick Hague and Russia’s Alexander Gorbunov are tasked with bringing them back early next year. This mission extends Wilmore and Williams' stay in space to over eight months.
title: SpaceX launches rescue mission for stranded Wilmore, Sunita Williams

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar criticized Pakistan at the UNGA, warning that its cross-border terrorism policy will not succeed and will have consequences. He emphasized that the key issue between India and Pakistan is the vacation of Pakistan-occupied Kashmir. This followed accusations from Pakistan PM Shehbaz Sharif about India's actions in Kashmir.
title: 'Actions will certainly have consequences': S Jaishankar warns Pakistan at UNGA

description: Chinese foreign minister Wang Yi reaffirmed China's strong support for Palestine’s legitimate rights and its bid for full UN membership during his address at the United Nations General Assembly. He called for an immediate ceasefire in Gaza, emphasizing a two-state solution as essential. Wang also addressed the ongoing war in Ukraine, urging de-escalation and promoting peace through dialogue.
title: 'We support full UN membership of Palestine': China at UNGA

description: A protest march took place in Jammu & Kashmir’s Budgam after Hezbollah chief Hassan Nasrallah was killed by the Israel Defence Force. Mehbooba Mufti cancelled her election campaign for a day to show solidarity with Palestine and Lebanon. Nasrallah, who became secretary-general of Hezbollah in 1992, transformed the group into one of the most powerful militant organizations in the Middle East.
title: Protests erupt in J&K's Budgam over killing of Hezbollah chief Nasrallah

description: The IPL Governing Council has decided that each franchise can retain up to five players and use one Right to Match (RTM) before the upcoming mega auction. If all five players are retained, it will cost the franchise Rs 75 crore from their total auction purse. The retention price caps are set at different amounts for each player retained.
title: IPL franchises set to shell out Rs 75 crore to retain five key players

description: Mayank Yadav has earned his maiden call-up to India's squad for the three-match T20I series against Bangladesh beginning on October 6. Suryakumar Yadav will captain the team while Hardik Pandya returns. Test regulars Shubman Gill, Yashasvi Jaiswal, and Rishabh Pant have been given a break.
title: Mayank Yadav gets maiden India call-up for Bangladesh T20Is

description: Hezbollah confirmed that its leader Hassan Nasrallah was killed in Israeli airstrikes. Hashem Safieddine is considered a likely successor. The article details recent eliminations of key figures from Hezbollah and Hamas by Israel, highlighting the ongoing conflict following Hamas' October 7 attack on Israel.
title: Who is Hashem Safieddine, the cleric likely to head Hezbollah after Nasarallah

description: Tamil Nadu's Udhayanidhi Stalin has been appointed deputy chief minister in a major cabinet reshuffle. The swearing-in ceremony is scheduled for September 29 at Raj Bhavan, Chennai. This move emphasizes Udhayanidhi's increasing influence within the DMK party and aims to solidify the party's position ahead of forthcoming elections.
title: Udhayanidhi Stalin named Tamil Nadu deputy chief minister, swearing-in on Sunday

description: The 'Bad Blood' Premium Live Event makes a comeback to WWE after over two decades. Fans eagerly anticipate the return of other classic PPVs such as Extreme Rules, Hell in a Cell, Unforgiven, Armageddon, and TLC. Each of these events is celebrated for its thrilling matches and distinctive stipulations for years.
title: Armageddon, Unforgiven and other classic WWE PPV’s that should return after Bad Blood

description: Punjab chief minister Bhagwant Mann was hospitalized in Mohali after experiencing pulmonary artery inflammation and testing positive for leptospirosis. He is being treated with antibiotics and has shown significant improvement. His vitals are stable, but he will remain under observation for further medical evaluation.
title: Punjab CM Bhagwant Mann tested positive for leptospirosis

description: BCCI secretary Jay Shah announced a match fee of Rs 7.5 lakhs per game for IPL players, allowing them to earn up to Rs 1.05 crore per season. This move is expected to benefit emerging and uncapped players significantly. The IPL Governing Council may finalize decisions on player retentions and Right to Match options in the upcoming auction.
title: 'Kya idea hai sir ji': Fans hail Rs 7.5 lakh per game IPL move

description: People's Democratic Party chief Mehbooba Mufti announced a one-day pause in her J&K assembly election campaign to stand in solidarity with Palestine and Lebanon following Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah's death. Jammu and Kashmir elections are being held in three phases, with the final phase on October 1 and results on October 8.
title: Mehbooba Mufti cancels campaign for a day after Hezbollah leader's death

description: Security forces confronted terrorists during a cordon and search operation in Kog-Mandli village, Kathua district, Jammu and Kashmir. Reinforcements were sent to neutralize the threat. The encounter began around 5.30 pm when police, army, and CRPF teams entered the forested area village. As of the latest reports, the search operation was still ongoing.
title: Encounter breaks out between security forces and terrorists in J&K's Kathua
Mobile internet to be suspended for 8 hours in Assam on Sunday

description: Afghanistan captain Hashmatullah Shahidi made a surprising choice by excluding MS Dhoni from his all-time ODI World XI. Instead of Dhoni, he selected Pakistan's Rashid Latif as the wicketkeeper. His lineup includes cricket greats like Saeed Anwar, Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, Kumar Sangakkara, Inzamam-ul-Haq, Mahela Jayawardene, Andrew Flintoff along with bowlers Rashid Khan, Waqar Younis and Jasprit Bumrah.
title: No Dhoni! Shahidi surprises with Pak keeper as his pick in ODI XI

description: ​The King send a birthday wish to Prince Harry as the prince turned 40 hinting at a thawing of their relationship caused by the hurt that Prince Harry delivered by badmouthing the Royal Family and then quitting the royal responsibilities. But a public birthday wish is the most King Charles would do, a meeting may not happen but nobody is ruling out a meeting as well.
title: Queen Camilla does not want King Charles to meet Prince Harry because...

description: BCCI secretary Jay Shah announced a match fee of Rs 7.5 lakhs per game for IPL players, leading to potential earnings of Rs 1.05 crores for those playing all league matches, excluding contract amounts. The IPL retention rules and auction details are expected to be finalized soon after the Governing Council meeting.
title: For IPL players, Jay Shah introduces match fee of Rs...

description: Rahul Gandhi has written to External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar, urging swift action for the release of 37 Tamil fishermen detained by Sri Lankan authorities. Tamil Nadu CM M K Stalin also sought intervention, highlighting the financial burden due to hefty fines imposed by Sri Lankan courts and calling for legal assistance and early release.
title: Rahul writes to Jaishankar about TN fishermen arrested in Sri Lanka

description: BJP leaders condemned Rahul Gandhi's remarks about the Ram Mandir consecration ceremony, where he alleged that farmers and laborers were excluded in favor of business tycoons. They defended the event's inclusivity and accused Gandhi of disrespecting Hindu beliefs and misunderstanding Indian culture, sparking significant political controversy.
title: BJP fires back at Rahul over 'nach-gaana' remark: 'First-class liar'

description: Israel executed airstrikes on Hezbollah positions in Lebanon, targeting over 140 sites and killing multiple commanders, including leader Hassan Nasrallah. Iranian deputy commander Abbas Nilforushan was also among the casualties. This week has seen one of the deadliest escalations since the 2006 war between Israel and Hezbollah, with over 700 deaths reported.
title: How Israel executed operation 'New Order' to kill Hezbollah leader Nasrallah in Beirut

description: The Government has lifted the ban on international exports of non-basmati white rice, implementing a minimum export price of $490 per tonne. Originally imposed to enhance domestic availability, the ban has been revoked effective immediately. The Directorate General of Foreign Trade confirmed this policy amendment, which will remain in effect until further notice.
title: India lifts ban on non-basmati white rice export, sets MEP at $490 per tonne

description: Kane Williamson surpassed Virat Kohli in the all-time Test run-scoring chart during New Zealand's ongoing match against Sri Lanka. Despite being dismissed for just 7 runs in the first innings, he bounced back with a solid 46 in the second innings. However, New Zealand continued to struggle and were reeling at stumps on day three.
title: Virat Kohli surpassed! Williamson reaches new milestone

description: 57-year-old Maya, a lawyer and a public policy advisor, said she is very proud to be part of Kamala Harris' presidential campaign and the feeling is extraordinary, electric. "I am just so proud to be able to be out there in these states encouraging people to knock on every door, call every voter, text their friends and family members between now and Election Day, to really have those personal conversations that help people learn who Kamala is, what she's fighting for, why they believe in her," Maya told People magazine.
title: Harris' sister says she will call her 'Madam President' when she's elected

description: Ayatollah Ali Khamenei condemned Israel’s airstrikes in Lebanon that killed Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah, calling them short-sighted. He urged support for Hezbollah and dismissed Israel’s ability to weaken the group. The strikes have caused significant casualties, marking the deadliest period of violence in Lebanon since its civil war.
title: 'Short-sighted and stupid': Khamenei slams Israel after Nasrallah's killing

description: Rahul Gandhi paid an emotional tribute to late CPM leader Sitaram Yechury, recounting their last meeting and urging him to seek medical attention. Gandhi praised Yechury for bridging ideological divides and his behind-the-scenes role in political alliances. He shared personal memories, emphasizing Yechury's integrity, dedication, and the profound loss he endured with his son's passing.
title: 'That was the last time I saw my friend': Rahul Gandhi remembers Sitaram Yechury

description: Parthiv Patel has clarified that Hardik Pandya is unlikely to return to Test cricket due to physical limitations. Although Hardik was seen practicing with a red ball, he hasn't played a first-class match since December 2018 and missed this year's Duleep Trophy. His body may not withstand the rigors of longer formats.
title: Parthiv dismisses Hardik's Test comeback rumours

description: In Revenge of the Tipping Point, Gladwell notes that Caltech, a highly competitive university with a merit-based admissions system, saw the proportion of Asian American students rise from 25% to 43% between 1992 and 2013. In contrast, at Harvard, where the admissions process is influenced by factors such as legacy, donor contributions, and athletic scholarships, the percentage of Asian American students has remained consistently between 15-20% during the same period. Indian applicants face even greater challenges in gaining admission through Harvard's selection process.
title: ‘Indian applicants likely to be excluded from Harvard’s application process’

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra reminisced about a trip to Jammu and Kashmir with her grandmother Indira Gandhi days before her assassination. She visits Kheer Bhawani Mata temple in Srinagar to honor her memory. Priyanka criticized the BJP for treating Jammu and Kashmir as a political pawn instead of focusing on its progress.
title: '4-5 days before assassination ... ': Priyanka recalls J&K trip with Indira Gandhi

description: Taylor Swift and Katy Perry are planning double dates with their partners Travis Kelce and Orlando Bloom after mending their relationship in 2018. The two singers have maintained a strong bond since then. Rumors suggest Kelce's performance is declining due to distractions, but his career achievements remain noteworthy.
title: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce plans on a double date with Katy Perry and Orlando

description: Chief Election Commissioner Rajiv Kumar and his team met with stakeholders in Maharashtra ahead of the assembly elections. Political parties urged that election dates take into account festivals like Diwali. Security measures are planned to ensure fair elections. The contest will be between the Maha Vikas Aghadi coalition and the Maha Yuti Alliance.
title: 'Parties told us to announce poll dates keeping Diwali in mind': CEC on Maha elections

description: Kane Williamson experienced a rare difficult day in the second Test against Sri Lanka, getting out twice within four hours. He was first dismissed by Prabath Jayasuriya and later by Nishan Peiris. New Zealand struggled at Galle International Stadium and was forced to follow on, now five wickets away from a series defeat.
title: Williamson dismissed twice in 4 hours : Here is how

description: A passenger on an Air India flight from Delhi to New York reported finding a cockroach in her omelette, resulting in food poisoning for her and her child. The airline is investigating the matter and reviewing its catering protocols to prevent similar incidents in the future.
title: Air India flyer finds cockroach in omelette on Delhi-NY flight, airline responds

description: Himachal Pradesh minister Vikramaditya Singh has reassured the Congress high command about his dedication to party ideology amid concerns over his remarks on street vendors. He clarified that the Uttar Pradesh model is not being adopted in Himachal Pradesh. An all-party committee will address street vending issues on October 3, focusing on law and order.
title: 'Will not do anything against ...': Vikramaditya clarifies street vendor remarks

description: A helicopter crash in North Waziristan, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, has led to seven fatalities and seven injuries. The chartered flight was transporting oil company employees when it experienced engine failure shortly after takeoff. The crash occurred during an emergency landing attempt. An investigation is ongoing to determine the cause of the technical fault.
title: Pakistan helicopter crash: 6 killed in North Waziristan, many injured

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, speaking at a rally in Hisar, Haryana, accused Congress of misleading Himachal Pradesh voters with false promises and highlighted internal conflicts within the party. He also criticized Congress for being anti-Dalit and praised BJP's initiatives for farmers. Modi expressed gratitude to those contributing to Haryana’s development on Bhagat Singh’s birth anniversary.
title: Watch: PM Modi's 'kya hua tera wada' jibe at Congress in Haryana

description: In Jammu and Kashmir's Kulgam district, two unidentified terrorists were killed while five security personnel, including an officer, sustained injuries during a gunbattle in Adigam village. The encounter began during a cordon-and-search operation early in the morning. Additional Superintendent of Police Mumtaz Ali was among those injured. Authorities are working to identify the slain terrorists.
title: 2 terrorists killed, 5 security personnel injured in encounter in J&K

description: Following orders from a special court for elected representatives, Bengaluru police have filed a criminal case against Union finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman and other officials. They are accused of extorting thousands of crores through electoral bonds. The case was prompted by an RTI activist's complaint earlier this year seeking investigation into the matter.
title: Criminal case registered against Sitharaman, others in Bengaluru

description: Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah's death in an Israeli airstrike is expected to significantly impact the group he led for 32 years. The challenge of finding a successor is compounded by internal and external pressures. Israel's military is preparing for potential escalations as tensions with Lebanon continue to rise following recent conflicts.
title: Who will lead Hezbollah after Hassan Nasrallah's death

description: In the County Championship Division One match between Somerset and Hampshire, Shoaib Bashir was initially saved from being bowled out due to a towel dropping from Kyle Abbott's trousers, causing distraction. The umpire ruled it not out, but Bashir was dismissed LBW three balls later. Somerset concluded their innings at 136 runs.
title: Watch: How a dropped towel saved a batsman from losing his wicket

description: Israel reported that it had killed Hezbollah leader Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah in an airstrike on Beirut's southern suburbs, also allegedly killing top commander Ali Karaki. The Israeli military indicated the strike aimed at disrupting Hezbollah’s terrorist plans against Israel, escalating concerns about potential involvement from Iran and the United States.
title: 'Ready for wider escalation': What Israel said on Nasrallah's killing

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath accused Congress of delaying the Ram Temple construction in Ayodhya and creating national problems. He credited BJP's rise under PM Modi for resolving the issue in 2019. Adityanath also highlighted development under BJP's leadership and criticized Congress for various crises faced by India.
title: ‘Should've been built in 1947’: Yogi says Cong stalled Ram Temple construction

description: Continuous rainfall has led to severe flooding in Nepal, causing at least 39 deaths and leaving 11 people missing. The capital Kathmandu and surrounding areas like Lalitpur and Bhaktapur are heavily affected. Around 3,000 security personnel are involved in rescue efforts as authorities issue warnings about potential flash floods.
title: 39 dead, several missing after heavy rainfall triggers floods in Nepal

description: Lionel Messi's two-decade-long career features major triumphs with FC Barcelona and Argentina. He has won 10 La Liga titles, four UEFA Champions League titles, and led Argentina to victories in the 2022 FIFA World Cup and two Copa America. Additionally, Messi has secured eight Ballon d'Or awards, underscoring his legendary status in football.
title: Messi's major trophies: From FIFA World Cup to Champions League

description: Quick Heal Technologies has alerted consumers about rising cyber threats with the upcoming festival season. These include fake shopping websites mimicking legitimate ones, malicious banking reward apps, counterfeit IRCTC apps stealing credentials, gift card scams, income tax refund frauds, and QR code phishing attacks aimed at harvesting personal and financial information.
title: IRCTC & 5 other big online scams that people are losing money to

description: In campaign rallies in Jammu and Kashmir, Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath claimed that Pakistan would soon be divided into three parts and cease to exist as it is known today. He warned that those spreading terror in India at Pakistan's behest would face severe consequences, referencing the strained relations over the Indus Water Treaty.
title: Pakistan will soon split into 3 parts, yearn for every drop of water: Yogi

description: Assam chief minister Himanta Biswa Sarma reported that Assam Police pushed back nine Bangladeshis and eight children early Saturday morning. This move comes after five Bangladeshis were apprehended for attempting to enter Karimganj district illegally. Security has been tightened along the Indo-Bangladesh border due to recent unrest in Bangladesh. Security has been tightened not only by the BSF but also by Assam Police personnel, taking guard as the second line of defence.
title: 17 'Bangladeshi' infiltrators sent back from Assam: CM Himanta Biswa

description: Akriti Chopra, co-founder and chief people officer at Zomato, has resigned effective immediately to pursue other interests. Having joined the company in 2011, she played a pivotal role in its financial and operational development. Her resignation follows shareholder concerns about governance issues related to Zomato's acquisition of Blinkit in 2022.
title: Zomato co-founder Arkriti Chopra resigns: Read 'resignation email' to CEO

description: The second day of the second Test between India and Bangladesh in Kanpur was called off due to persistent rain. The weather forecast predicts more rain on Sunday, but sunny conditions on Monday and Tuesday. Bangladesh had finished the first day at 107 for three, with India leading the series 1-0.
title: India vs Bangladesh, 2nd Test: Rain washes out second day in Kanpur

description: YSRCP leaders conducted purificatory rituals in response to allegations by Andhra Pradesh CM Nara Chandrababu Naidu about adulterated ghee in Tirupati Laddu prasadams. They asserted that utmost care was taken during their regime and questioned the government's probe into the issue, calling for an independent investigation to uncover the truth.
title: Laddu controversy: YSRCP performs purification rituals at temples across Andhra

description: Rajkot police apprehended five individuals after a video depicting a birthday celebration on a public road gained widespread attention. The incident took place near Atal Sarovar on the new 150-foot Ring Road and included fireworks and vehicles blocking the road, creating potential hazards for public safety.
title: Five held for birthday bash on public road in Gujarat's Rajkot
Viral video: Police arrest 6 persons in Ghaziabad road rage incident

description: In northwest China, a woman named Li gave birth to twins from both of her uteruses, an extremely rare condition affecting just 0.3 percent of women globally. The healthy boy and girl were delivered at Xi’an No 4 hospital after eight and a half months of pregnancy. This remarkable case has garnered significant attention on social media.
title: Chinese woman with two uteruses delivers a baby from each
Bengaluru's Taj West End hotel gets bomb threat via email

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized the BJP for excluding farmers and laborers from the Ram Mandir Pran Pratishtha ceremony while inviting billionaires. He alleged that President Draupadi Murmu was barred due to her tribal background. Gandhi promised welfare measures like financial aid for women and filling vacant government jobs if Congress wins Haryana's upcoming elections.
title: Ram Mandir Pran Pratishtha had naach-gana, Adani but not one farmer: Rahul

description: In Harda, Madhya Pradesh, drones with thermal imaging are deployed to find a fugitive accused of raping a five-year-old girl. The suspect has been on the run for four days despite efforts by police and sniffer dogs. In Indore, authorities are investigating allegations of sexual harassment involving a three-year-old girl at a private school.
title: Heat-seeking drones on trail of child rapist in Madhya Pradesh forest

description: After a 15-year pursuit, Maoist commander Rupesh was killed in a week-long operation in Chhattisgarh's Bastar region. He was wanted for the assassination of SP Vinod Kumar Chaubey in 2009. Chaubey's son Saumil Ranjan Chaubey expressed mixed emotions about the encounter and stressed that dialogue is preferable to violence.
title: Chhattisgarh SP's Maoist killer hunted down after 15-year chase

description: Delhi saw clear skies and satisfactory air quality on Friday due to strong winds and rain in nearby areas, keeping the AQI at 80. Despite some stubble burning in neighboring states, it hasn't affected Delhi's air quality yet. The air is expected to remain satisfactory through Monday.
title: Once in a blue moon: Delhiites breathe easy, AQI drops to 80

description: Virender Sehwag's 309 in Multan during India's 2004 tour of Pakistan is one of Indian cricket's most iconic moments. He became the first Indian to score a triple century, sharing an amusing incident with Sachin Tendulkar. Their camaraderie and mutual respect on and off the field significantly benefited the Indian team.
title: 'Bat maarunga...': When Sachin warned Sehwag against hitting a six

description: Kamala Harris is slightly ahead of Donald Trump in most polls, and Asian diplomats are leaning towards supporting her in the upcoming US presidential elections. Analysts suggest that import tariffs might be lower under Harris compared to Trump. However, uncertainty looms for businesses managing supply chains in Asean economies due to unclear foreign policies towards Asia.
title: Harris, Trump and tariffs: Who has got Asian nod

description: A fire broke out early Saturday at Tata Electronics Private Limited's mobile phone accessories painting unit in Krishnagiri district. Employees were safely evacuated and seven fire tenders were dispatched to contain the blaze. Three workers experienced respiratory distress but are stable. The facility employs about 4,500 people, mainly women.
title: Massive fire breaks out at Tata Electronics Plant in Tamil Nadu

description: The September 27 episode of Friday Night SmackDown featured action-packed matches and engaging segments with Randy Orton, Cody Rhodes, Kevin Owens, and The Bloodline. Highlights included Bayley defeating Naomi to become the number one contender for the Women’s Championship and Carmelo Hayes winning against Andrade. The main event saw The Bloodline defeating Orton and Owens.
title: WWE SmackDown 9/27 Results

description: Arm recently made an inquiry to acquire Intel's product division that sells chips for PCs, servers, and networking equipment but was turned down. This development comes as Intel faces severe challenges and restructures its operations. Arm aims to expand into markets traditionally dominated by Intel while continuing its growth beyond smartphone chip designs.
title: Intel tells Arm its chip business 'not for sale'

description: A sewage pipe explosion in Nanning, China resulted in human feces being shot 33 feet into the air, drenching pedestrians and vehicles. The incident occurred during a pressure test on newly-installed pipes. No injuries were reported, but the force was strong enough to flip a digger. Cleanup operations began immediately.
title: Poo-nami in China: Sewage explodes sending feces up in air, passers-by drenched

description: Ranveer Allahbadia, popularly known as BeerBiceps, thanked YouTube for restoring his channels following a cyber attack. Hackers had taken over his primary channel, renaming it "Tesla," and altered its handle. Allahbadia reassured followers that the incident was not a marketing stunt and expressed gratitude for their support.
title: Ranveer Allahbadia thanks YouTube after all 'deleted' channels back

description: Terry Phelan, a former English Premier League player with stints at Manchester City and Chelsea, has embraced Indian football and is currently serving as the technical director of South United FC. He reflects on his journey from England to India, elaborating on the differences in sporting director roles and addressing challenges like age fraud in Indian football.
title: Age fraud in football: 'Many don't have birth certificates, like in Africa'

description: A gang of seven robbers from Haryana carried out three ATM heists in Kerala, stealing Rs 68 lakh. They used a container truck for their escape but were intercepted by police in Tamil Nadu following a high-speed chase. One robber was killed, and six others were apprehended.
title: Cash, chaos and chase: 'Fast & furious' ATM robbery spree ends in arrests

description: The IPL Governing Council plans to meet on Saturday in Bengaluru to finalize retention rules for the upcoming season. An official announcement is expected shortly, potentially by Sunday. The mega auction might occur in the Middle East towards late November, with decisions on its date also anticipated during this meeting.
title: IPL Retention Rules: Governing Council to meet today, decision soon

description: Elon Musk has been ordered to pay a $1.8 million fine to lift the ban on X in Brazil. The Brazilian court had shut down the platform after Musk refused to remove right-wing accounts and failed to appoint a legal representative. The company is now complying with the court's orders.
title: Musk faces $1.8 million fine for reinstatement of X in Brazil

description: Delhi High Court observed that teenage love cases are in a legal grey area, often involving girls over 17 who elope and then change their statements under parental pressure. This was highlighted while granting bail to a 22-year-old man accused of abducting a 17-year-old girl, noting discrepancies in her statements.
title: Teenage love in ‘legal grey area’, debatable to categorise as offence: HC

description: In Rangpuri Pahari, southwest Delhi, Heeralal Sharma killed his four daughters before dying by suicide. Neighbors alerted authorities due to a foul smell from their flat. Police found three packets of Celphos poison inside. Heeralal had been absent from work since January 2024 and struggled with family issues following his wife's death last year.
title: Delhi horror: Father commits suicide after killing 4 daughters

description: In Bhadrak district, mobile internet services were suspended following communal violence over a social media post. Protests against police inaction turned violent, injuring three officers. The district administration imposed prohibitory orders to ban gatherings and demonstrations indefinitely to prevent further unrest and ensure public safety.
title: 'Objectionable' post sparks violence in Odisha, internet shut for 48 hrs

description: Deputy chief minister Prem Chand Bairwa faced online backlash after his son appeared in a social media reel driving a modified jeep, escorted by a state government vehicle. Initially defending his son, Bairwa later apologized publicly, acknowledging the public's concern and emphasizing he did not want to cause issues for his party or himself.
title: Rajasthan deputy CM’s son seen with govt escort, sparks backlash

description: Babban Vishwanath Shinde, the primary suspect in the Rs 300 crore Jijau Masaheb Multi-State Bank scam, was captured in Vrindavan by Maharashtra police. Shinde allegedly misled depositors with promises of high returns and absconded with their funds. He has been transported to Maharashtra following a local court's remand order.
title: Living as sadhu, Rs 300 crore co-op bank scam accused arrested
EOW summons ticket booking firm CEO, its tech head over Coldplay event

description: Devara: Part 1 in Hindi made around Rs 7 crore on opening day which is also a good number, considering now Jr NTR's popularity in the northern parts of India, is also growing rapidly!
title: 'Devara: Part 1' box office collection day 1

description: An active encounter between security personnel and terrorists is taking place in the Adigam Devsar area of Kulgam district, Jammu and Kashmir. The Kashmir Zone Police announced this on social media, indicating that police and security forces are involved. Additional information is expected as the situation develops.
title: Encounter underway between security forces, terrorists in J&K's Kulgam

description: A dispute over using the old or new logo for IIM-A's The Red Brick Summit allegedly led to PGP student Akshith Bhukya’s suicide. His father lodged a complaint against a woman from the institute, prompting an investigation and event cancellation. Bhukya was found hanging in his hostel room, leading to further inquiries.
title: 'Old vs new logo' behind IIM student’s shocking suicide, dad tells cops

description: Diplomats exited during Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu's UN General Assembly speech, protesting Israel's military actions in Gaza and Lebanon. Netanyahu committed to ongoing strikes on Hezbollah in Lebanon despite international cease-fire efforts. The Gaza conflict has led to extensive destruction and displacement over nearly a year.
title: Diplomats walkout during Netanyahu's speech as Israeli airstrikes rage across Lebanon

description: In his memoir, former UK PM Boris Johnson disclosed that during the pandemic, he explored an aquatic raid on a Dutch warehouse to obtain AstraZeneca vaccines. The plan was discussed with military leaders in March 2021 and involved using boats and lorries to retrieve and transport the urgently needed vaccines back to the UK.
title: UK considered ‘aquatic raid’ on Netherlands to seize Covid vaccine: Boris

description: Three armed men opened fire at a car showroom in west Delhi's Naraina, firing over 25 rounds. The attack is believed to be part of an extortion racket involving gangster Himanshu Bhau. Fortunately, no injuries were reported. Police have initiated an investigation to identify and apprehend the shooters.
title: 'Bhau gang since 2020': Gangsters open fire in Delhi's car showroom

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella describes a true leader as one who brings optimism, energy, and clarity to solve complex issues. Addressing the productivity paradox where managers doubt employee effort while employees feel overworked, he advocates for data-driven leadership with clear goals and engaging events to bridge this gap.
title: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella says, for me a true leader is who …

description: In Kaimur district, a 23-year-old man died after being detained by police who suspected him of consuming alcohol while he was running to a hospital after a snake bite. His family alleges that the police demanded a bribe for his release, causing significant delays. Authorities have ordered an inquiry into the matter.
title: Bitten by snake, held by cops: 'Liquor check' kills victim in Bihar

description: India countered Pakistan Prime Minister Shebaz Sharif's UNGA remarks, accusing Islamabad of perpetuating cross-border terrorism. Indian diplomat Bhavika Mangalanandan cited examples like the 2001 Parliament attack and the 2008 Mumbai attacks. She emphasized that Jammu and Kashmir is an integral part of India, condemning Pakistan’s history of violence and election rigging.
title: 'Country run by military ... ': India slams Pakistan's Article 370, Kashmir claims at UNGA
‘Not required’: SC expunges HC remarks on conversions
STF arrests school ex-principal over paper leak in UP jobs test
4 cops, 2 government staffers held for molesting, abducting student

description: FOX Weather meteorologist Bob Van Dillen paused his live coverage of Hurricane Helene in Atlanta to save a woman trapped in her car by rising floodwaters. He carried her to safety before first responders could arrive. The hurricane left extensive damage and claimed at least 44 lives across Florida and the southeastern US.
title: Reporter halts live broadcast, jumps into water to save drowning woman

description: Iran condemned the US for supporting Israeli airstrikes on Gaza and Lebanon, accusing Israel of using American-supplied bombs. Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah was reportedly targeted but is believed to be safe. The US denied prior knowledge of the strikes, while President Biden directed adjustments to US forces in the Middle East.
title: '5k-pound bunker busters': Iran condemns US 'complicity' in Israeli strikes

description: Selectors have added pace bowler Mayank Yadav to a special camp at the National Cricket Academy before the T20I series against Bangladesh. They aim to evaluate his recovery from a recurring side strain and might include him in future international games, including the upcoming Test series against New Zealand.
title: 'Fit' Mayank Yadav in special camp ahead of T20Is against Bangladesh

description: Donald Trump has vowed to prosecute Google if he is re-elected, claiming the search engine shows only negative stories about him while favoring Kamala Harris. Google denied these allegations, asserting that both candidates' websites appear at the top for relevant searches. Trump did not provide any evidence to support his claims.
title: Bad news for Trump? Why former US prez vowed to prosecute Google

description: Sanjay Manjrekar raises concerns over Rohit Sharma's choice not to use Ravindra Jadeja against left-handed batsmen during day one of the second Test against Bangladesh. Highlighting Jadeja's past success, especially against Alastair Cook, Manjrekar notes Rohit's preference for Ashwin but emphasizes Jadeja's effectiveness.
title: Manjrekar 'educates' Rohit Sharma with a piece of stat

description: An office-bearer from Abhishek Banerjee's Camac Street office has accused Kolkata mayor Firhad Hakim's OSD, Kalicharan Bandyopadhyay, of extorting money using Banerjee's name. The complaint was lodged at Shakespeare Sarani PS. Mayor Hakim defended his OSD and questioned the need for a police complaint without prior departmental inquiry. A preliminary probe is ongoing.
title: Abhishek's office files 'extortion' plaint against Kolkata mayor's aide

description: Maldives President Mohamed Muizzu, during his visit to the US for the UN General Assembly, denied any 'India Out' agenda. He addressed concerns about foreign military presence and disciplined officials for insulting Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi on social media. Relations between India and Maldives have been tense since Muizzu's pro-China administration assumed office.
title: Maldives never opted for ‘India Out’ policy, asserts president Muizzu
EOW summons ticket booking firm CEO, its tech head over Coldplay event
Pakistan again rants against India over Kashmir, ‘threat to seize POK’

description: Israeli airstrikes targeted Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah in Beirut, resulting in numerous deaths and injuries. Despite the attack, Nasrallah is confirmed to be alive. This marks a significant escalation in the ongoing conflict between Israel and Hezbollah, with substantial impacts on both sides of the confrontation.
title: Who is Nasrallah? Hezbollah leader who was target of Israeli strikes
In war-hit Ukraine, Indian innovators lend hand to those who lost arms

description: Mitchell Starc faced a tough time in the fourth ODI against England at Lord's, as Liam Livingstone smashed 28 runs off his over, setting an unwanted record for the Australian bowler. Livingstone's 67 not out powered England to 312 for 5, leading to a decisive 186-run victory and leveling the series at 2-2.
title: Rohit Sharma 'nightmare' returns to haunt Starc - Watch

description: Kolhapur police have arrested a couple for allegedly strangling their son-in-law on a state transport bus. The couple confessed, claiming their daughter had threatened suicide if her husband was not stopped from harassing her. CCTV footage and witness accounts were crucial in identifying and apprehending the suspects.
title: Couple held on charge of killing son-in-law on moving bus

description: Residents of Shankar Nagar in Hyderabad face distress as their homes along the Musi River are marked for demolition despite having land ownership documents. They fear losing both homes and livelihoods. Authorities confirm no demolitions have occurred yet and assure rehabilitation in 2BHK houses according to policy before any action is taken.
title: Protests erupt as houses in Telangana's Shankar Nagar marked for demolition

description: The health crisis from the Musi belt may have reached Hyderabad's eastern corridor, as vegetables grown with contaminated Musi river water are sold in Uppal market. Farmers and traders admit to selling these potentially harmful vegetables due to livelihood constraints. Experts call for immediate government action to halt this practice.
title: Musi’s tainted waters serve up toxic platter in Hyderabad
PM hails India's rise in Global Innovation Index
STF arrests school ex-principal over paper leak in UP jobs test

description: Two Vasai traffic cops, a CISF jawan, an SRPF personnel, and two government employees have been arrested for allegedly molesting and attempting to abduct an 18-year-old nursing student in Sindhudurg district. The men were drunk and off-duty when passersby intervened. They have been suspended from duty and are currently in police custody.
title: Dragged to SUV: How drunk traffic cops, jawan, govt worker 'molested' nursing student

description: Mumbai police have stepped up security measures across the city, focusing on high-traffic places of worship after an Intelligence Bureau alert about a potential terror attack. Officers are performing mock drills in crowded areas and religious sites. Deputy commissioners are actively monitoring these efforts ahead of upcoming festivals and assembly elections.
title: Mumbai on high alert: Intelligence Bureau warns of possible 'terror attack'
